comments: Jackson Jr. (MEM) engages and disengages with Gay (SAS) off-ball.
Gay (SAS) slightly extends his hands forward into Allen's (MEM) left side as the pick is set and makes marginal contact.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) makes contact across Murray's (SAS) left arm after his gather, then turns into Murray's body as he is airborne during the driving shot attempt.

Murray (SAS) makes incidental contact with Morant's (MEM) face/left arm after Morant jumps toward him during rebounding. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Morant (MEM) makes incidental body contact with Murray (SAS) as they each attempt to retrieve the rebound.
Brooks (MEM) lowers his left shoulder and veers  into White's (SAS) front and initiates contact that dislodges White from position after his gather.
Morant (MEM) makes contact across Murray's (SAS) left arm preventing him from gaining control of the rebound.
Johnson (SAS) makes marginal body contact with Allen's (MEM) side at the end of the drive.
Brooks (MEM) makes marginal body contact with DeRozan (SAS) as he brings the ball into the front-court.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) makes marginal contact with DeRozan's (SAS) extended left leg after the release of his driving shot attempt.
Brooks (MEM) makes marginal body contact with DeRozan's (SAS) side after his gather.
Brooks (MEM) goes to, not through, Morant's (MEM) space as contact occurs to Morant's backside during the inbound. Morant's reaction is not consistent with the level of contact.
White (SAS) wraps Clarke's (MEM) right side as they roll toward the lane. After communicating with the scorer's table, it was determined that MEM was not in the bonus at the time of the foul.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) extends slightly into White's (SAS) path prior to contact occurring during the screen, but it is marginal.
White (SAS) briefly has his arm around Clarke's (MEM) upper half before correcting.
Gay (SAS) makes marginal contact with Morant's (MEM) front/side at the end of the drive.
Morant (MEM) leaves his feet and his left foot returns to the floor prior to when he releases the ball.
Gay (SAS) firms up in his screening position prior to contact occurring with Brooks (MEM), which Gay absorbs.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) moves underneath DeRozan (SAS) and initiates contact with DeRozan's lower half that affects his ability to safely land.
Morant (MEM) cleanly deflects the inbound pass intended for Gay (SAS). After communicating with the Replay Center, the call on the floor of SAS ball was confirmed.
Mills (SAS) and Clarke (MEM) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Brooks (MEM) and White (SAS) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) makes marginal contact with White's (SAS) right arm at the start of his dribble.
Clarke (MEM) commits the take foul on DeRozan (SAS).

Gay (SAS) makes slight contact with the top of Morant's (MEM) head during rebounding.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Gay (SAS) and Jackson Jr. (MEM) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Morant (MEM) and White (SAS) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Gay (SAS) contest Jackson's Jr. (MEM) shot attempt and does not cross his defensive plane or restrict Jackson's follow through.
Brooks (MEM) is drawn toward DeRozan (SAS) on the pump fake and initiates contact with DeRozan's body during his upward shooting motion.
Brooks (MEM) establishes himself in a screening position in Johnson's (SAS) path and does not deliver the contact.
